#compdef stash
# =============================================================================
# stash — Stashapp's media organization server — a Go-
#          implemented HTTP server + Vue.js web UI that
#          catalogues a user's local media collection by
#          scanning configured folders, extracting
#          metadata (file size, duration, codec, perceptual
#          hash, scene markers), and exposing a queryable
#          GraphQL API for tagging, search, and external
#          integrations.  Stores all metadata in a SQLite
#          database; media files remain on disk
#          untouched.
#          Distinguishing from plain file managers (no
#          metadata index), Plex / Jellyfin / Emby (focused
#          on streaming with transcoding; less flexible
#          tagging; non-extensible metadata schemas),
#          digiKam (KDE photo manager; not media-server-
#          shaped), and home-built spreadsheet catalogues
#          by:
#            - GQLGEN-FOUNDATION GRAPHQL API — uses
#              99designs/gqlgen v0.17 (this is the
#              headline CLI library that CONTINUES Axis
#              46 on the Go side; see taxonomy notes
#              below) for the entire HTTP query
#              surface.  All UI interactions, scraper
#              integrations, and third-party clients
#              communicate via GraphQL.  Every Stash
#              feature is API-first
#            - PERCEPTUAL HASHING via go-imagehash —
#              uses corona10/goimagehash for perceptual
#              image hashing of scene thumbnails;
#              enables near-duplicate detection without
#              exact byte equality
#            - DISINTEGRATION/IMAGING — uses
#              disintegration/imaging (Axis 40 Image
#              Processing companion library; same lib
#              used by R750 Go=95 pigo) for thumbnail
#              generation and image manipulation
#            - HEADLESS-CHROME SCRAPER INTEGRATION —
#              uses chromedp/chromedp + chromedp/
#              cdproto for headless-browser scraping
#              of metadata from configurable scraping
#              endpoints; lets users enrich their
#              local index with external metadata
#              sources
#            - HTMLQUERY for HTML-SCRAPING — uses
#              antchfx/htmlquery (Axis 41 HTML
#              Parsing companion; same family as
#              R754 Go=96 besticon's goquery) for
#              XPath-based HTML parsing of scraped
#              pages
#            - GQLGENC TYPED-CLIENT GENERATION —
#              uses Yamashou/gqlgenc to generate
#              typed Go clients for upstream GraphQL
#              APIs; enables federated scraping from
#              other Stash instances or external
#              GraphQL services
#            - SQLITE STORAGE via go-sqlite3 + golang-
#              migrate — uses mattn/go-sqlite3 with
#              the golang-migrate v4 migration
#              framework for schema versioning; users
#              can rollback database schema across
#              Stash version updates
#            - SUBTITLE PARSING via go-astisub —
#              uses asticode/go-astisub for parsing
#              SRT/VTT/ASS subtitle formats; enables
#              full-text search within subtitle
#              tracks
#            - SORT-ORDER NATURAL — uses WithoutPants/
#              sortorder for natural human-friendly
#              sorting (e.g. "scene10" after "scene2"
#              not before)
#            - PFLAG CLI — uses spf13/pflag for the
#              minimal command-line interface; most
#              configuration happens in the
#              config.yml file read at startup, not
#              via flags
#            - DESKTOP-INTEGRATED MODE — bundled
#              `desktop` package supports launching
#              into a system tray + auto-opening the
#              browser window; `--nobrowser` disables
#              this for headless server deployments
#            - VUE.JS FRONTEND — bundled webui (Vue
#              + TypeScript) served from `ui/`
#              package via embedded assets; no
#              separate frontend deployment needed
#            - PHASHER COMPANION BINARY — separate
#              `phasher` binary (in cmd/phasher) for
#              standalone perceptual hashing of media
#              files; useful for CI-driven hash
#              generation outside the main server
#              process
#            - 12,434+ STARS ON stashapp/stash —
#              one of the most popular Go-based
#              GraphQL applications by stars in the
#              corpus; AGPL-3.0 license; active
#              development by a community of
#              maintainers; documentation at
#              https://docs.stashapp.cc
#          Used by: home-server enthusiasts cataloging
#          local media libraries, archivists building
#          searchable indexes over collected files,
#          and developers studying production Go +
#          GraphQL + Vue.js application architecture
#          (the codebase is regularly cited as a
#          reference for gqlgen-based server
#          patterns).
#
# Author:  Stashapp community + maintainer team at
#          github.com/stashapp.  Repository at
#          stashapp/stash; documentation at
#          docs.stashapp.cc.  AGPL-3.0 license.
# Source:  https://github.com/stashapp/stash
#          https://github.com/stashapp/stash/blob/develop/cmd/stash/main.go
#          https://github.com/stashapp/stash/blob/develop/internal/manager/config/init.go
#          https://github.com/stashapp/stash/blob/develop/go.mod
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; `stash --help`
#          shows pflag-generated flag list; full
#          configuration documentation at
#          https://docs.stashapp.cc
# Library: github.com/99designs/gqlgen v0.17.73
#          (Alexandre Bezroutchko + 99designs's "go
#          generate based graphql server library").
#          This is the headline dependency for this
#          completion's axis-46 continuation role;
#          see taxonomy notes below.  Also spf13/
#          pflag (Axis 1 argparse), Yamashou/
#          gqlgenc (typed GraphQL client generation),
#          mattn/go-sqlite3 (SQLite), golang-migrate/
#          migrate v4 (schema migrations),
#          disintegration/imaging (Axis 40 image
#          processing; same as R750 pigo),
#          antchfx/htmlquery (Axis 41 HTML parsing;
#          alternative to goquery used by R754
#          besticon), corona10/goimagehash
#          (perceptual hashing), chromedp/chromedp +
#          chromedp/cdproto (headless-browser
#          scraping), asticode/go-astisub (subtitle
#          parsing), WithoutPants/sortorder (natural
#          sorting), anacrolix/dms (DLNA media
#          server).
# License: AGPL-3.0
# Status:  12,434+ stars on stashapp/stash; very
#          active development; multi-maintainer
#          community; one of the largest Go GraphQL
#          applications by adoption + star count
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY — AXIS 46 CONTINUES:
#   GRAPHQL SERVER / GRAPHQL RUNTIME (Go side)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This completion **CONTINUES AXIS 46** in the cross-
# language CLI library taxonomy.  R773 Rust=101
# (tailcall/async-graphql OPENS Axis 46) → R774 Go=101
# (stash/99designs/gqlgen CONTINUES Axis 46 THIS
# ROUND).  Pending: R775 TS-Node=101 with an apollo-
# server or graphql-yoga user to close Axis 46 at
# 1/1/1.
#
# WHY 99designs/gqlgen IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-46
# CONTINUATION:
#
#   github.com/99designs/gqlgen is the dominant Go
#   GraphQL server library — the canonical CODE-
#   FIRST + SCHEMA-FIRST hybrid approach where users
#   write a GraphQL SDL schema, run `go generate`,
#   and gqlgen emits typed resolver interfaces +
#   model structs that the user implements.
#   Distinguishing characteristics:
#     1. SCHEMA-FIRST + CODE-GENERATED — write
#        schema.graphql, run `go generate`, get
#        type-safe Go interfaces.  Compare to
#        Rust's async-graphql (CODE-FIRST: write
#        Rust structs, derive macros generate
#        schema) — gqlgen INVERTS this with
#        SCHEMA-FIRST + RESOLVER-INTERFACE
#        generation
#     2. TYPED RESOLVERS — the generated interfaces
#        force users to implement every query +
#        mutation + subscription with type-correct
#        Go signatures; impossible to ship a
#        partially-implemented resolver
#     3. FEDERATION SUPPORT — implements Apollo
#        Federation v2 (`@key`, `@external`,
#        `@requires`, `@provides`); compatible with
#        apollo-router + grafbase + tailcall
#        federation gateways
#     4. SUBSCRIPTIONS via WEBSOCKET — supports
#        graphql-ws + graphql-transport-ws protocols
#     5. DATALOADER PATTERN — companion graph-
#        gophers/dataloader library for batching +
#        caching of resolver fetches
#     6. PLUGIN ARCHITECTURE — gqlgen.yml
#        configuration drives the codegen; users
#        can write custom plugins for additional
#        type-conversion or directive handling
#     7. ~10,723+ STARS ON 99designs/gqlgen — by
#        far the most-starred Go GraphQL library
#     8. ECOSYSTEM-DOMINANT — used by stash (this
#        completion), pentagi, capact, dagger,
#        99designs's own production services, and
#        thousands of other Go GraphQL projects
#
# Maintained under github.com/99designs/gqlgen.
# License: MIT.
#
# Cross-language CLI library taxonomy after R774:
#   * 125 languages
#   * 482 total CLI library variants (Rust 101 /
#     Go 101 / TS-Node 100)
#   * Axis 9 / Logging: 6/6/6 three-language symmetric
#   * Axes 10 + 13 + 14: 2/2/2 three-language symmetric
#   * 38 axes at 1/1/1 three-language symmetric
#   * Axis 46 continues with Rust=async-graphql +
#     Go=99designs/gqlgen; pending TS-Node companion
#
# Comparison to other Axis 46 candidates (Go):
#   * stash (R774 THIS) — Stashapp media organizer
#     with gqlgen v0.17.73 as direct dep; 12,434
#     stars; very large + active GraphQL
#     deployment
#   * pentagi — pentesting AI agents; 17,384 stars,
#     uses gqlgen v0.17.57 directly; LARGER but
#     dual-use security-context tool (per project
#     authorization-context guidelines)
#   * dagger — already in corpus as `_dagger`
#   * tyk — already in corpus
#   * apex/up — already in corpus
#   * capact — 79 stars, niche
#   * go-proto-gql — 217 stars, protobuf converter
#   * gqlgenc — generated client library, not CLI
#     itself
#
# stash is the chosen Axis 46 Go-side continuation
# because:
#   - It uses 99designs/gqlgen as a DIRECT runtime
#     dependency in go.mod (`github.com/99designs/
#     gqlgen v0.17.73`)
#   - The GraphQL-everywhere architecture pattern
#     is the textbook gqlgen use case — every
#     server interaction (UI, scraping, third-
#     party integration) uses the same GraphQL
#     schema
#   - 12,434 stars + multi-maintainer community
#     make it a stable taxonomy choice
#   - Active development + well-documented codebase
#     make it a frequently-cited reference for
#     production Go + GraphQL patterns
#   - AGPL-3.0 license adds license-distribution
#     diversity (most corpus entries are MIT/
#     Apache/BSD)
#
# Pending companion pick for Axis 46:
#   - TS-Node=101: a Node.js CLI tool prominently
#            using @apollo/server (Apollo GraphQL's
#            official server library; ~14,000+
#            stars) OR @graphql-yoga/node (The
